12,http://www.armslist.com/posts/988012,"For Sale:  Aimpoint Micro H-1, 4 MOA","Southern, Indiana, United States",$ 620,"Listed On: Sunday, February 10, 2013",Optics,Sig Sauer                                                                                ,223/5.56 NATO                                                                                ,Semi-automatic                                                                                ,Rifle,"Item is brand new, never used in original packaging.

No matter what your mission, the size and weight of your equipment is a critical factor. With the Aimpoint Micro H-1, Aimpoint has introduced an aiming system that provides the performance of full-sized sights in the smallest package possible. Designed with the hunter in mind, these sights are the lightest red dot sights tough enough to bear the Aimpoint name. Small enough to be used anywhere that you could put iron sights, these sights can be used on any type of firearm or archery equipment. A lightweight rifle with Micro H-1 mounted on it remains a lightweight rifle. A hunting revolver with a Micro H-1 installed remains as easy to carry as with iron sights and is much quicker to aim. On a bow, the parallax-free Micro H-1 eliminates the need for a peep, allowing you to shoot accurately in lower light.

Built to offer the same battle-proven ruggedness as other Aimpoint products, the Micro H-1 is able to perform under extreme conditions while adding negligible weight to your weapon. Suitable for use on rifles, carbines, shotguns, and handguns, the Aimpoint Micro H-1 is ideal as a stand-alone sight, and because it weighs less than 4 ounces including the integrated Weaver mount, it can easily be “piggybacked” on top of larger magnifying scopes optics.
Aimpoint's unique band-pass coating on the front lens gives the highest possible dot brightness, while providing the clearest, brightest image possible.
Features 13 brightness settings for use in daylight and low-light conditions, so the Micro H-1 is ready for use around the clock.
Unique Features of the Micro H-1:
- Ideal for rifles, carbines, shotguns, and handguns
- 1x (non-magnifying) parallax-free optic
- Integral Weaver-style mount allows easy attachment to any rail
- Patent pending mount is keyed to the sight body to absorb recoil
- New ACET technology allows 50,000 hours (over 5 years) of constant operation from one battery
- 4 MOA dot
- 13 brightness settings for use in daylight and low-light conditions
- Matte Black finish
- Submersible to 15 feet (5 meters)
- Precision adjustments for windage and elevation. Top of protective caps fits into holes on adjustment screws – no other tool required
- Use as a stand alone sight or “piggybacked” on larger magnifying optics
I will ship anywhere. Paypal, and USPS money orders accepted."

Trijicon TA31A ACOG 4x32 Scope with Red Dual Illumination Triangle Reticle BAC features Dual Illumination (Fiber Optic provides daylight illumination and imagetritium illuminates reticle at night). The reticle of the Trijicon Rifle Scope ranges out to 800 Meters for 5.56 (.223 cal). Trijicon 4 x 32mm ACOG Advanced Combat Optical Gunsights TA31A hit fast in any light. Trijicon ACOG 4 x 32 Riflescopes TA-31A are internally-adjustable, compact telescopic sights with tritium illuminated reticle patterns for use in low light or at night. Bindon Aiming Concept (BAC) models feature bright daytime reticles using fiber optics which collect ambient light. Trijicon 4x32 ACOGs combine traditional, precise distance marksmanship with close-in aiming speed. Although Trijicon ACOG 4 x 32 Rifle Scopes TA31-A have many features which are very advantageous for military use, they were developed by Trijicon without government funding. Designed for use with the M16 family, every feature of its mechanical and optical design was chosen for a single purpose: to provide increased hit potential in all lighting conditions - without failure-prone batteries."

The 3XMag is a revolutionary tool for military personnel, law enforcement, sport shooters and hunters. When combined with Aimpoint's patented TwistMount, the 3XMag gives the user something never before possible – the ability to switch in a split second from CQB (Close Quarters Battle) to semi-sniping and vice versa. Hunters can rapidly switch from non-magnifying to magnifying while still being able to keep their Aimpoint sight on their firearm. The versatile 3XMag also can be used as a handheld magnifying glass monocular for discrete observation and identification.
The recommended mount for the 3XMag is the Aimpoint Twist Mount, which allows for quick attachment and detachmen. The Aimpoint TwistMount fits any MIL-Std 1913 Picatinny Rail.
